  "body": "I'm not sure where to make documentation update requests, but if I had this in the docs it would've saved me hours or struggling\r\n \r\nwhen using rancher's RKE the kubetlet runs as a docker instance\r\nwhich mean the host's volume-plugin-dir needs to be mounted as a docker volume.\r\n\r\nThis can be done via the cluster.yml as\r\n\r\n```\r\nkubelet:\r\n    image: \"\"\r\n    extra_args:\r\n      volume-plugin-dir: /usr/libexec/kubernetes/kubelet-plugins/volume/exec\r\n    extra_binds:\r\n    - /usr/libexec/kubernetes/kubelet-plugins/volume/exec:/usr/libexec/kubernetes/kubelet-plugins/volume/exec\r\n```\r\n\r\nand the rook operator.yml\r\n```\r\nenv:\r\n- name: FLEXVOLUME_DIR_PATH\r\n   value: \"/usr/libexec/kubernetes/kubelet-plugins/volume/exec\"\r\n```",
